The paper deals with the problem of self-interference cancellation in full-duplex communication, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is based on Kalman filter theory, which is a common tool in control systems (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of communication rate, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
